I have analyzed the GitBook API documentation for organizations. Here are some key points:

- The API base URL is https://api.gitbook.com/v1
- Endpoints include listing organizations, getting organization details, updating organizations, deleting invites, joining organizations, searching organizations, and listing organizations by email domain.
- All endpoint cURL commands include headers: Content-Type: application/json and Accept: application/json
- The documentation does not explicitly show the authentication method in the endpoint examples, but based on GitBook API standard practice, it uses Bearer Token authentication with an access token.

I suggest configuring the connector group for GitBook with Bearer Token authentication, where the user will provide an access_token.

Here is the proposed auth configuration for the connector group:

```json
{
  "type": "bearerToken",
  "details": {
    "expires_in": {
      "type": "number",
      "hidden": true,
      "default": 100000,
      "disabled": true
    },
    "access_token": {
      "type": "password",
      "required": true,
      "description": "Token"
    }
  }
}
```

I will now proceed to create the GitBook connector group with this authentication configuration.
